  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> and finely slice 3 rings per person, then dice the <strong>remaining onion</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> onion rings</strong> and your<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>to a shallow bowl and set aside to pickle until serving – these are your <strong>quick-pickled onion rings</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> as finely as you can, including the stalks</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> in a bowl<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>herby mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> beef mince</strong> to the pan, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Add your<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>soy sauce</strong>, then cook for a further 8-10 min or until the beef mince is cooked (no pink meat!) and starting to crisp – this is your <strong>smoky beef mince</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, pat it dry with kitchen paper, then separate the<strong> outer leaves </strong>and finely shred the <strong>inner core[s]</strong></p><p>Drain and finely dice your <strong>pineapple slices</strong> (don’t chuck the pineapple juice down the drain. Instead, add it to your smoothies or marinades!)</p><p>Combine the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong>, <strong>diced pineapple </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) in a bowl with plenty of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>pineapple salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.-step-5.new-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1156.-step-5.new-x400.jpg",
